It may be time to drop gold and tech stocks and buy into South Africa’s domestically focused stocks, according to JPMorgan Chase & Co. The broker upgraded its view on South African equities to overweight from underweight this week, saying the global value trade driven by faster economic growth, stronger commodity prices, a weaker dollar and fewer trade tensions with the incoming US administration will benefit domestic stocks such as banks and value cyclicals, at the expense of gold and tech firms. Black Friday SpecialGet 15% discount on our annual subscription!
